daniel thursz a former executive vice president of b'nai b'rith international died on tuesday at his home in bethesda md he was 71 the cause was a heart ailment the organization said at his death dr thursz was the cardinal o'boyle professor of social work at catholic university of america where he earned a master 's degree in 1955 and a doctorate in 1960 he is survived by his wife hadassah neulander thursz three daughters deborah t bleiweis of cortlandt manor ny and deena t klopman and tamar t truland of north potomac md a son david of baltimore and eight grandchildren

